					<TextView
						android:id="@+id/story"
						android:layout_width="match_parent"
						android:layout_height="wrap_content"
						android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
						android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"
						android:padding="8dp"
						android:text="My dear young scholars, as you embark on your academic journey, I offer you these words of wisdom from an old man who has seen it all.\n\nFirstly, remember that knowledge is power, but wisdom is key. Seek knowledge with all your might, but also seek wisdom to apply it.\n\nSecondly, never stop learning. The moment you think you know it all is the moment you begin to fail.\n\nThirdly, respect your lecturers, but do not be afraid to question them. Critical thinking is the hallmark of a true scholar.\n\nFourthly, do not let grades define you. Your worth goes beyond your GPA.\n\nFifthly, make time for extracurricular activities. The skills you learn outside the classroom are just as important as those you learn within.\n\nSixthly, build relationships with your peers and mentors. The networks you build now will benefit you in the long run.\n\nSeventhly, do not be afraid to fail. Failure is not the end, but a stepping stone to success.\n\nLastly, remember that your education is not just for yourself, but for the betterment of society. Use your knowledge to make a positive impact in the world.\n\nMay these words guide you as you navigate the halls of academia. May you emerge as wise, knowledgeable, and compassionate individuals, ready to make a difference in our great nation, Nigeria."
						android:textSize="12sp"
						android:textColor="#000000"
						android:lines="6" />
