					<TextView
						android:id="@+id/story2"
						android:layout_width="match_parent"
						android:layout_height="wrap_content"
						android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
						android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"
						android:padding="8dp"
						android:text="The anxiety I felt as I left my children, Chiamaka and Chukwuebuka, alone at home for the first time! I had to attend a crucial meeting at work, and their father was away on a business trip. I had no choice but to leave them in charge of themselves for a few hours.\n\nAs I drove away from the house, my mind raced with thoughts of all the potential dangers and mishaps that could occur. What if they forgot to lock the door\? What if they played with the stove and caused a fire\? What if... what if... what if...\n\nBut as I arrived at the meeting and began to focus on the discussions, I realized that I had to trust my children to be responsible. After all, I had raised them to be independent and resourceful.\n\nWhen I returned home, I was relieved to find the house still standing and my children safe and sound. In fact, they had even managed to prepare a simple meal for themselves and clean up after themselves! I was impressed and proud of their resourcefulness.\n\nLeaving my children alone for the first time was a difficult experience, but it taught me to trust in their abilities and to know that they are capable of taking care of themselves. And as a mother, that is the greatest lesson of all."
						android:textSize="12sp"
						android:textColor="#000000"
						android:lines="6" />
